8:
Are you sure about this? Because
I'm not...
12:
To gather information is to seek it
out directly. That is what the book
Stella lent me said.
20:
It will be fastest if I show myself and
do the asking. Let's go.
25: Gaze closely. Do you recognize me?
28:
Huh? Who're you? And... why are you
so pale?! You okay, dude?
32:
Don't look at the face. Look at the
armor. Do you know who made this
armor—
37:
Oookay, Londahl, that's enough! I'm
gonna stop you right there!
53:
*pant* I'd tell you to use your head,
but it's clear you don't got one!
57: Sorry. I forgot how to turn this neck.
59: Hehe, in a spot of trouble, are we?
65:
Why, I've come to save you...
sentient armor that you are.
68: You... Do you know about me?
71:
Of course! An armor with a will of its
own, capable of bestowing great
power to its wearer. You're rather
well known among my people.
72:
I'd heard you vanished many years
ago, but I'm delighted to see you've
returned!
74:
My offer is simple: won't you change
hosts?
76:
I'm well aware of your situation
already. I can offer you a far
superior host than the half-dead
body you're dragging around.
78:
Come find me when you've made
up your mind. I'll be waiting.
81:
Are you going to take her up on that
offer?
85: It would make sense for me to.
92:
Lloyd will die, as I'm the only thing
keeping him alive.
99:
Are you really all right with that
outcome, Londahl?
102:
I want to meet my creator. That is
my sole goal.
115:
I'm always serious. Stay out of my
way.
120:
One of these fellows behind me will
become your new host. Why don't
you unbind yourself from that shell
of a man? Release the spell.
124:
Hehehe, I'm sure your one wish will
come true soon, my dear sentient
armor.
132: I... have a name? But why? How? I...
134:
I suddenly don't want to unbind
myself.
137:
*sigh* Just whose idea was it to give
the armor a will of its own?
140: Get rid of that walking corpse!
145:
It's okay. You're allowed to.
There's always room for dessert.
158:
At this point, Lloyd feels like one of
us, you know? Besides...
162:
Had a feeling you didn't have your
mind made up yet.
